==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Successful
<hw>Suc*cess"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Resulting in
success; assuring, or promotive of, success; accomplishing what was
proposed; having the desired effect; hence, prosperous; fortunate;
happy; <as>as, a <ex>successful</ex> use of medicine; a
<ex>successful</ex> experiment; a <ex>successful</ex>
enterprise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Welcome, nephews, from <qex>successful</qex> wars.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Happy; prosperous; fortunate; auspicious; lucky.
See <er>Fortunate</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Suc*cess"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Suc*cess"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succession</ent>⟦br⟧
